#rd-navbar.panel
	.panel-header
		h3.panel-title RD Navbar
	.panel-body
		p RD Navbar is a jQuery plugin for creating a navigation panel.
		p Plugin and style sheets linking occurs when the element that matches the #[code .rd-navbar] selector is present on the page.
		p An example of plugin operation is available on the following page: #[a( href='navbar.html' ) Navbar].

		p An example of the simplest markup:
		pre.highlight.html.scroller.scroller-horizontal
			='<div class="rd-navbar-wrap">\n'
			='  <nav class="rd-navbar">\n'
			='    <ul class="rd-navbar-nav">\n'
			='      <li class="rd-navbar-nav-item"><a class="rd-navbar-link"></a></li>\n'
			='      <li class="rd-navbar-nav-item"><a class="rd-navbar-link"></a></li>\n'
			='      <li class="rd-navbar-nav-item"><a class="rd-navbar-link"></a></li>\n'
			='      <li class="rd-navbar-nav-item"><a class="rd-navbar-link"></a></li>\n'
			='    </ul>\n'
			='  </nav>\n'
			='</div>'

		p All RD Navbar parameters are configured only in initialization.
		p All available parameters of the plugin can be viewed on #[a( href="http://cms.devoffice.com/coding-dev/rd-navbar/documentation" ) RD Navbar] website.
